28/03/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Kasyanov visited Bucharest Thursday (27 March) to discuss texts of a draft economic partnership agreement that will likely be signed in May or June. It is expected to boost large cross-border projects involving the transit of oil and gas.
In other news Thursday, Croatia and Slovenia extended by three months their agreement on boat crossings and fishing in their common sea border. Tensions rose last summer following a spate of incidents at sea. (Nine O'Clock; Rompres - 28/03/03; HINA - 27/03/03)
